description.narrative: By 2023 MoEYS at all levels has enhanced capacity to plan, execute and monitor results-based plans and budgets., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Evaluation And Research, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2023, girls and boys, particularly the rural and urban poor, have increased access to inclusive, equitable, relevant and quality early childhood and basic education that promotes lifelong learning, including in emergencies.
